		<title>Trump on best behavior as he woos Republicans but differences remain</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump went on a charm offensive on Thursday to try to win the party establishment's support for his insurgent candidacy, but top Republican Paul Ryan stopped short of endorsing him.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Obama administration to issue transgender restroom guidance to schools</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - The Obama administration will tell every U.S. public school district on Friday to allow transgender students to use the bathrooms that match their gender identity.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=zNzGJOZHE2s:mmGL3uu63K4:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=zNzGJOZHE2s:mmGL3uu63K4:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?i=zNzGJOZHE2s:mmGL3uu63K4:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=zNzGJOZHE2s:mmGL3uu63K4:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?i=zNzGJOZHE2s:mmGL3uu63K4:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>Trump says he and Ryan close on border security, trade and military: Fox News</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump said on Thursday that he and U.S. House of Representatives Speaker Paul Ryan largely agree on issues of border security, trade and beefing up the military.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Republicans win Obamacare legal challenge, add to insurer concerns</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - A U.S. judge on Thursday handed a victory to congressional Republicans who challenged President Barack Obama's signature healthcare law, ruling that his administration overstepped its constitutional powers relating to government spending.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>U.S. foreign policy veteran warns Trump would make world less stable</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Donald Trump's foreign policy proposals would make the world a less stable place, former Secretary of State James Baker told a U.S. Senate hearing on Thursday as the Republican presidential candidate met elsewhere with party congressional leaders.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Exclusive: U.S. plans new wave of immigrant deportation raids</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. immigration officials are planning a month-long series of raids in May and June to deport hundreds of Central American mothers and children found to have entered the country illegally, according to sources and an internal document seen by Reuters.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=-pe3yQn4r2g:IMj_-9JAhws:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=-pe3yQn4r2g:IMj_-9JAhws:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?i=-pe3yQn4r2g:IMj_-9JAhws:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=-pe3yQn4r2g:IMj_-9JAhws:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?i=-pe3yQn4r2g:IMj_-9JAhws:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>U.S. probes Trump's former butler for urging Obama assassination</title>


		<description>NEW YORK (Reuters) - The U.S. Secret Service is investigating presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump's former butler over a Facebook post calling for President Barack Obama's assassination.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Senator Rand Paul to back bill blocking FBI hacking expansion</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Kentucky Senator Rand Paul plans to become the first Republican co-sponsor of legislation to block a pending judicial rule change that would let U.S. judges issue search warrants for remote access to computers located in any jurisdiction, his office told Reuters on Thursday.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Senate sets votes on competing Zika funding plans</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Three competing plans for battling a potential Zika virus outbreak in the United States were presented on the floor of the U.S. Senate on Thursday, as lawmakers tried to break an impasse pitting President Barack Obama against congressional Republicans.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Cuba and U.S. officials to meet next week to deepen detente</title>


		<description>HAVANA (Reuters) - Cuba and the United States will meet next week for a third round of talks on improving relations, Havana said on Thursday, adding that the two former Cold War foes were not yet negotiating their multibillion-dollar claims against one another.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=L3uLtcTajuE:ceFloMdiYz8:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=L3uLtcTajuE:ceFloMdiYz8:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?i=L3uLtcTajuE:ceFloMdiYz8:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?a=L3uLtcTajuE:ceFloMdiYz8:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/PoliticsNews?i=L3uLtcTajuE:ceFloMdiYz8:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>
